Greek Alphabet (24 letters):

N=Name, L=Lowercase, U=Uppercase, T=Transliteration
E=Erasmian pronunciation, M=Modern pronunciation

  N       L    U   T              E                M
---------------------------------------------------------------
Alpha     α    Α   a       f(a)ther
Beta      β    Β   b       (b)ook            (v)at
Gamma     γ    Γ   g       (g)oat            (g)oat or (y)ellow
Delta     δ    Δ   d       (d)og             (th)is
Epsilon   ε    Ε   e       (e)pic
Zeta      ζ    Ζ   z       a(dz)e            (z)oo
Eta       η    Η   ē       (a)pe             f(ee)t
Theta     θ    Θ   th      (th)ink
Iota      ι    Ι   i       (i)gloo or sk(i)  sk(i)
Kappa     κ    Κ   k       (k)eep
Lambda    λ    Λ   l       (l)id
Mu        μ    Μ   m       (m)oon
Nu        ν    Ν   n       (n)oon
Xi        ξ    Ξ   x       a(x)
Omicron   ο    Ο   o       d(o)g
Pi        π    Π   p       (p)epper
Rho       ρ    Ρ   r/rh    (r)ed             r (trilled)
Sigma     σ/ς  Σ   s       (s)ing            (s)ing or (z)ero
Tau       τ    Τ   t       (t)op
Upsilon   υ    Υ   u       m(oo)n            f(ee)t
Phi       φ    Φ   ph/f    (f)ind
Chi       χ    Χ   ch/kh   lo(ch)
Psi       ψ    Ψ   ps      hi(ps)
Omega     ω    Ω   ō       d(o)g

The 7 vowels: α, ε, ι, ο, υ, η, ω

A diphthong is a combination of two vowels pronounced as
a single sound. There are 8 diphthongs:

αι   (ai)sle    b(e)t
ει   w(ei)ght   f(ee)t
οι   b(oi)l     f(ee)t
αυ   h(ow)      (af)fect or (av)enue
ου   s(ou)p     p(oo)l
υι   s(ui)te    f(ee)t
ευ   f(eu)d     (ef)fect or (ev)erywhere
ηυ   f(eu)d     iyf or iyv
